        <span class="scrub-demo-readout"><span class="scrub-demo-value">0</span>%</span>
      </div>
    </figure>
  </div>
</section>

<hr class="rule"/>

<section class="cs-system flip">
  <div>
    <p class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--accent-cbc-light);">System 02</p>
    <h3>Critters with somewhere to be</h3>
    <p>Each critter is a small data object — a definition asset, a set of garden conditions it cares about, and a State Tree that decides what to do moment to moment. The lifecycle is its own machine: critters wander past, decide a garden is worth visiting, settle in if it stays good, and leave when it isn't. No big behavior file. Just clean little pieces talking to each other.</p>
    <span class="cs-tag">State Tree</span><span class="cs-tag">UCritterDefinition</span><span class="cs-tag">Conditions</span>
  </div>
