<section class="section narrow">
  <h2>What I've learned so far</h2>
  <p>Building this slowly has taught me to push back on my own urge to over-engineer. The critter system started life as a tangle of components and inheritance; it's now five small pieces that don't know much about each other. The cardboard material had four layers, then three. The grid was a Procedural Mesh, until it wasn't.</p>
  <p>Cutting things has been most of the work — and most of the fun.</p>
</section>

